# 3. Re-install
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

# 4. Verify version (if this works without crashing, the Segfault is gone)
minikube version

```

### 🐳 Docker Way (Memory Check)

Sometimes Docker runs out of resources, causing the Minikube driver to crash.

```bash
# Check if your system has enough RAM/Storage
free -m
df -h

# Restart Docker to clear hung memory segments
sudo systemctl restart docker

# Try starting minikube again
minikube start --driver=docker

```

